A cozy Singapore HDB apartment interior in Studio Ghibli style, showing a whimsical custom-built children's loft bed with hidden compartments, ladder, and play nooks integrated into warm wooden design. Soft afternoon light streams through large windows revealing distant high-rise buildings. Scattered across a low coffee table are colorful magazines and fabric swatches. A laptop sits open nearby displaying 3D furniture blueprints on screen. Moving boxes are stacked in corners, suggesting transition and new beginnings. The room feels hopeful and creative, with potted plants adding life. Warm color palette of honey wood tones, soft greens, and gentle yellows. Gentle, dreamy atmosphere with characteristic Ghibli attention to domestic detail and lived-in charm.
